China seen producing 1 . 6 mln vehicles in 1997 . China ' s production of motor vehicles is expected to rise by 100 , 000 to 1 . 6 million in 1997 , the China News Service said on Friday . Demand for cars for private use and rental was forecast to increase this year , the news agency said . A crackdown on smuggling and illegal assembly of cars and motorcycles was expected to boost sales of locally - made cars , especially sedans , it said . China ' s car market slumped last year with production racing ahead of demand . The gross output value of China ' s auto industry was estimated at 230 billion yuan ( $ 27 . 7 billion ) in 1996 , the news agency said without giving further details . ( $ 1 = 8 . 3 yuan ) 
